&lt;p data-start=&quot;61&quot; data-end=&quot;136&quot;&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong data-start=&quot;82&quot; data-end=&quot;102&quot;&gt;Business Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; to join &lt;strong&gt;the Quality Control team&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;138&quot; data-end=&quot;391&quot;&gt;The team safeguards the quality of operations across every division at Plata. Supported by a large team of specialists and AI-driven quality monitoring, we identify operational issues, process gaps, and improvement opportunities across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;393&quot; data-end=&quot;746&quot;&gt;In this role, you will own the quality improvement loop end-to-end: analyzing findings, identifying root causes, coordinating stakeholders, and ensuring issues are resolved rather than simply reported. You will work closely with operational, product, analytics, and training teams to improve processes, drive efficiency, and enhance customer experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;748&quot; data-end=&quot;906&quot;&gt;This role offers direct visibility into how the company operates at scale and the opportunity to influence quality standards across multiple business domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Challenges that await you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor quality dashboards and metrics across our operational and product teams to spot anomalies, gaps, and recurring issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dig into the root cause of every issue — across operations, product, the knowledge base, and the technical setup — to understand &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; it happens, not just &lt;em&gt;that&lt;/em&gt; it happens&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the quality-improvement loop end-to-end: turn raw findings from our QC platform into a clear, prioritized action plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate fixes across operational and product teams: set tasks with the right owners, agree on timelines, and follow through until they’re closed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and prioritize a backlog of quality issues and plan their resolution quarter by quarter&lt;/li&gt;
